            "use strict";
            __webpack_require__.r(__webpack_exports__);
            /* harmony default export */ __webpack_exports__["default"] = ("<p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-0\">IT RISK AND SECURITY</p>\n\n<div class=\"row\">\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n    <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/IT Risk _ Security.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">\n            Organizations today are under ever-increasing pressure to comply with regulatory\nrequirements, maintain strong operational performance, and increase shareholder value. In\nthis hyper-competitive environment, organizations can no longer afford ad-hoc security\nmeasures. Protecting intellectual property, sensitive customer information, and other\nbusiness-critical information requires a comprehensive security strategy that closely matches\nbusiness objectives.\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"homep\">Our security practice is dedicated to providing you with world-class security advice. This\n            advice is based on our global knowledge and experience of providing security consulting services governing strategy, design, configuration, and assessment of enterprise security\n            together with identifying/accessing management solutions to our clients.</p>\n     <p class=\"homep\">CySpace Global™ Risk &amp; Security solutions provide accurate risk assessments and\n            systematic implementation of security management tools.<br />\n            We will help you identify, monitor and predict your IT problems of which include\n            security operations, identify and access management, governance, and compliance as\n            well as advisory services where we advise you on any problem you might encounter.</p>       \n            <p>Tools - Cybereason/ TrendMicro, Radware, crowd strike, Anomali</p>\n\n        <p class=\"color\">\n            PACE YOUR SECURITY STEPS TO ACE THE\n            THREATS\n        </p>    \n    </div>\n\n<p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-0\">SECURITY OPERATIONS</p>\n\n<div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n                <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/Security Operations.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n          \n              </div>\n\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">\n            In this age of rapidly advancing technology, businesses big and small must protect sensitive\n            information about their clients, employees, partners, internal operations and more. But with\n            the rising sophistication of cybercriminals and hacking software, this protection has become\n            an increasingly challenging task. Look through our Security operations services and tools for\n            your requirements.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n    <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-1\"> MANAGED SECURITY SERVICES</p>\n    <ul class=\"self\">\n                       <li>We offer managed security services for the oversight and administration of a\n                        company’s security processes. CySpace Global™ conducts services either in-house\n                        or remotely, typically via the cloud.</li>\n                       <li>We offer a wide range of security services, from setting up infrastructure\n                        through security management or incident response. Some managed security service\n                        providers specialize in certain areas while others offer full outsourcing of an\n                        enterprise’s information security program.</li>    \n                       <li>The primary benefit of managed security services is the security expertise\n                        and additional staffing they provide. The ability for CySpace Global™ to manage\n                        security processes from an off-site location allows enterprises to conduct business as\n                        usual with minimal intrusion due to security initiatives, while we interface maintains a\n                        constant line of communication and seamless reporting to the business. (Learn More)</li>        \n            </ul>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n    <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-0\">Our Manages Security Services include below services</p>\n    <ul class=\"self\">\n        <li>Behavior Analytics - At CySpace Global™ we continuously monitor user behavioral\n                analytics is to reveal the actions users take within a digital product. It organizes raw\n                event data such as clicks into a timeline of each user&#39;s behavior, also known as a\n                user journey.<br />Tools - Observe IT, SIEM, PSM</li>\n        <li>Consulting Services - Accelerate your journey to a digital enterprise. our consulting\n                services focus on strategy, execution, and optimization to help clients achieve true\n                business transformation that is IT enabled and future-ready</li>\n        <li>Database Security - Database security refers to the collective measures used to\n                protect and secure a database or database management software from illegitimate use and malicious threats and attacks. It is a broad term that includes a multitude of\n                processes, tools, and methodologies that ensure security within a database\n                environment.</li>\n        <li>Data Protection - The challenge of data privacy is to use data while protecting an\n                individual's privacy preferences and their personally identifiable information.[3] The\n                fields of computer security, data security, and information security design and use\n                software, hardware, and human resources to address this issue with their Local data\n                protection policies &amp;Regulations like GDPR/HIPPA</li>  \n         <li>End Point Security - Endpoint security or endpoint protection is an approach to the\n                protection of computer networks that are remotely bridged to client devices. The\n                connection of laptops, tablets, mobile phones and other wireless devices to corporate\n                networks creates attack paths for security threats.\n                Tools- Carbon black, Cylance, crowd Strike, Cylance, McAfee, Microsoft defender,\n                Symantec</li>\n        <li>Firewall and network protection - A firewall is a network security device that monitors\n                incoming and outgoing network traffic and decides whether to allow or block specific\n                traffic based on a defined set of security rules. <br />\n                Tools- Open DNS, Fortinet FortiGate, Palo Alto Networks, SonicWall, Barracuda,\n                Cisco Firepower, Check Point Advanced Threat Protection, Juniper Networks,\n                Huawei</li> \n        <li>Security Information and Event Management (SIEM)</li>                            \n    </ul>\n  </div>\n    <p class=\"homep\">Who is looking at your log files to determine if an event is happening? Our SIEM service\n            provides log aggregation, log monitoring, event analysis and 24X7 response to critical\n            severity events. This service leverages commercial SIEM tools as well as custom tools and\n            methodologies to determine important events and then correlate, validate and alert on those\n            events by:</p>\n     <p class=\"homep\">Security Information and Event Management (SIEM)</p>       \n     <ul class=\"self\">\n         <li>Providing log aggregation for the most common systems, firewalls, email appliances, web\n                filtering, domain controllers, servers, anti-virus and IPS devices.</li>\n     </ul>\n     <!-- <p class=\"homep\">Managed Security Operations Centre</p>       \n     <p class=\"homep\"> \n        Our Managed Security Operation center operate in 24/7/365 model and my team comes up with vast experience with certification like CEH, CISA, CISSP and they regularly provides below services\n     </p>\n     <ul>\n         <li>Security Monitoring</li>\n        </ul>\n        <ul>\n         <li>Security Event Monitoring</li>\n        </ul>\n        <ul>\n         <li>Security Intelligence</li>\n        </ul>\n        <ul>\n            <li>Log Management & Compliance Reporting</li>\n        </ul> -->\n\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-2\">SECURITY INTELLIGENCE</p>\n\n<div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n                <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/Security Operations.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\" height=\"216px\">\n          \n              </div>\n\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">\n        Security intelligence is the information relevant to protecting an organization\n        from external and insider threats as well as the processes, policies, and tools\n        designed to gather and analyze that information.\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"homep\">CySpace Global&trade; enables your company to prevent data breaches, secure\n        personal and sensitive information and detect security events, attacks, and incidents.</p>\n    </div>\n    </div> \n        <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-3\">CHANGE AND CONFIGURATION COMPLIANCE</p>\n        <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n                <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/change-and-configuration-compliance.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n          \n              </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">\n        In the modern IT environment, there is a seemingly endless number of\nbusiness processes being supported by IT. As these processes mount, it becomes\nnecessary to implement and meet a veritable mountain of internal and external\nregulatory compliance requirements in an effective manner that is both efficient and\nsustainable.\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"homep\">We provide automated solutions and tools to provide non-stop, real-time\n        detection of vulnerabilities.</p>\n    </div>\n    </div> \n\n    <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-4\">Managed Firewall services</p>\n<div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n                <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/managed-firewall.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n          \n              </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">\n        CySpace Global™ offers a wide range of managed IT security\nservices to organizations of all sizes to safeguard investments and\nmeet compliance regulations. Managed Firewall Services includes\n    </p>\n    <p><b>Managed Firewall Services:</b> CySpace Global™ delivers 24x7 administration, monitoring, and\n        maintenance of client firewall infrastructure to preserve availability,\n        integrity, and privacy of information and defend against threats.</p>\n\n        <p><b>Managed Next-Generation Firewall:</b> CySpace Global™ Provides 24x7 operational administration,\n                monitoring and maintenance of client next-generation firewalls with\n                threat intelligence to enhance blocklist functionality.</p>\n        <p><b>Managed Web Application Firewall:</b> CySpace Global™ Delivers 24x7 management and real-time\n                monitoring of web application firewalls, with support for the entire\n                WAF lifecycle: powerful protection without interrupting legitimate\n                traffic.</p>        \n        <p><b>Managed IDS/IPS:</b> CySpace Global™ Provides 24x7 monitoring, maintenance, and\n                administration of IDS/IPS technology to eliminate malicious traffic\n                with powerful countermeasures.</p>        \n    </div>\n    </div> \n\n    <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-5\">VULNERABILITY MANAGEMENT</p>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n                    <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/Vulnerability-Management.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n              \n                  </div>\n    \n      <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n        <p class=\"homep\">\n                The primary goal of the Vulnerability Management is to reduce cyber risk, by\n                continually identifying, assessing, and tracking vulnerability remediation through closure\n                to reduce risk to your organization&#39;s perimeters. <b>Vulnerability management</b> is the key\n                process for identifying and assessing security weaknesses before they are exploited.\n                <b>Vulnerability assessment</b> results in mitigation activities to remove the risk or allow\n                management of an organization to formally accept risk.\n        </p>\n        </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-6\">THREAT MANAGEMENT AND MODELLING</p>\n\n        <div class=\"row\">\n                <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n                        <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/Storage managementThreat-Management and Modelling.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n                  \n                      </div>\n          <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n            <p class=\"homep\">\n                With a centralized approach to detecting and preventing advanced security\n                threats, our Threat management service is focused on a prevention-first approach\n                across all managed laptops, workstations, Macs, and servers, moving past previous\n                reliance on purely signature-based detection. Our service leverages next-generation\n                capabilities incorporating artificial intelligence and machine learning, combined with\n                application/script control, memory protection, and device policy enforcement.\n            </p>\n            <ol>\n                  <li>Delivering real-time protection with global oversight and risk reduction measures\n                        across all your devices.</li>  \n                  <li>Uses AI to detect potential threats and delivers malware prevention capabilities.</li>  \n                  <li>With the help of AI, a centralized view of all the security is enabled.</li>  \n                  <li>Cloud-based, lightweight and low impact</li>  \n                  \n            </ol>\n            <p><b>1. Global Threat Intelligence</b></p>\n            <p class=\"homep\">Our threat intelligence supported by tons of technology partners and\n                hundreds of penetration testers spread across the world.</p>\n                <p>CySpace Global™ Provides 24x7 Constant monitor and updates cloud-\n                        based threat intelligence metrics ensures faster update over newly\n                        discovered malware enabling us offering stronger resistance even\n                        against zero-day vulnerabilities.</p>\n            <p><b>2. Advanced Threat Detection & Management Services</b> </p>            \n            <p>Advanced Threat Services\n                CySpace Global™ Prevent the threats you can and leverage cyber\n                threat intelligence and global visibility to detect and respond to the\n                threats you can’t prevent.</p>\n             <p><b>3. Advanced Endpoint Threat Detection</b></p>   \n             <p>CySpace Global™ Delivers 24x7 monitoring of endpoint activity so you\n                know when an advanced threat actor penetrates your defenses, which\n                systems are compromised, how they got in and how to remove them as\n                early as possible.</p>\n              <p><b>4. Advanced Endpoint Threat Prevention</b></p>  \n              <p>Protect your users and dramatically reduce the effort required to stop\n                advanced threats that target your endpoints, no matter where or how\n                they work.</p>  \n               <p><b>5. Advanced Malware Protection and Detection</b></p>   \n               <p>CySpace Global™ has specialized security analysts combine vast\n                intelligence with advanced technology to help you see, rapidly analyze\n                and diagnose targeted zero-day threats.</p>      \n\n            </div>\n            </div>\n\n <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-7\">PSM/PAM (PRIVILEGE SESSION MANAGEMENT / PRIVILEGE ACCESS\n        MANAGEMENT)</p>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n                    <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/PSM-PAM.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n              \n                  </div>\n      <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n        <p class=\"homep\">This service provides reliant and consistent, refined processes and tools for\n                the management of privileged accounts in your organization. These processes and\n                tools are designed to enable privileged make privileged accounts protected airtight\n                while scaling down the impact vastly on the administrators and services that utilize\n                them. As privileged accounts are usually highly targeted, it is imperative for the\n                organizations to value their security.</p>\n        </div>\n        </div>\n\n\n\n\n\n        <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-8\">NETWORK OPERATIONS</p>\n\n        <div class=\"row\">\n                <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                        <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/Network operations.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid imgmar\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n                      </div>\n          <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n            <p class=\"homep\">\n                Today's network architecture is complex and is faced with a threat environment that is\n                always changing and attackers that are always trying to find and exploit vulnerabilities.\n                These vulnerabilities can exist in a broad number of areas, including devices, data,\n                applications, users and locations. For this reason, there are many network security\n                management tools and applications in use today that address individual threats and exploits\n                and regulatory non-compliance.\n            </p>\n           </div>\n           <p class=\"color\">PIONEERING THE ENGINEERING OF SECURITY</p>\n\n           </div>\n        \n           <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-9\">CYBER ATTACK MITIGATION</p>\n        \n        <div class=\"row\">\n                <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                        <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/Cyber attack migration.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n                      </div>\n          <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n            <p class=\"homep\">\n                Organizations must marshal advanced detection capabilities and deploy a\n                coordinated response across security, IT, risk and business stakeholders to minimize\n                the impact of an attack. CySpace Global™ provides a solution to stay vigilant and\n                tackle any emerging cyber-attacks from old or new source.\n            </p>\n           </div>\n           </div>\n        \n           <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-10\">VULNERABILITY ASSESSMENT</p>\n        \n        <div class=\"row\">\n                <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                        <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/vulnerability Assestment.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n                      </div>\n          <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n            <p class=\"homep\">\n                Vulnerability testing helps organizations identify vulnerabilities in their\n        software and supporting infrastructure before a compromise can take place. There\n        are three primary objectives of a vulnerability assessment. </p>\n                <ul type=\"a\">\n                    <li>Identify vulnerabilities ranging from critical design flaws to simple\n                        misconfigurations.</li>\n                    <li>Document the vulnerabilities so that developers can easily identify and\n                        reproduce the findings.</li>    \n                    <li>Create guidance to assist developers with remediating the identified\n                        vulnerabilities.</li>    \n                </ul>\n                <p class=\"homep\">Whether your organization develops applications or uses third-party\n                    applications, vulnerability testing annually, or after significant changes to the\n                    applications or application environments are implemented, it is critical to ensure a\n                    rock-solid security initiative.</p>\n           </div>\n           </div>\n        \n           <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-11\">INTERNET SECURITY</p>\n        \n           <div class=\"row\">\n                <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                        <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/internet Security.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n                      </div>\n             <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n               <p class=\"homep\">\n                Internet security is implemented by the tasks and tools you use to prevent\n                unauthorized people or programs from accessing your networks and the devices\n                connected to them. CySpace Global™ provides the right solutions, per your\n                requirements and data.</p>\n                </div>\n                </div>\n        \n                <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-12\">PEN-TESTING</p>\n        \n                <div class=\"row\">\n                        <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                                <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/pentesting.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n                              </div>\n                  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n                    <p class=\"homep\">\n                        The main objective of penetration testing is to identify security weaknesses.\n                        Penetration testing can also be used to test an organization&#39;s security policy, its\n                        adherence to compliance requirements, its employees&#39; security awareness and the\n                        organization&'s ability to identify and respond to security incidents. Penetration testing is the practice of testing a computer system, applications,\n                        networks and/or web applications to find vulnerabilities through ethical hacking.</p>\n                        <ul   class=\"self\">\n                            <li>Determining the scope of work and type of technical testing services the\n                                organization wishes to have performed</li>\n                            <li>Performing the following using PCI-QSA, CISSP, and CISA-certified personnel:   \n                            <ul>\n                                <li>Scanning the various devices</li>\n                                <li>Demonstrating how an attack would be made by attempting attacks, either\n                                    bypassing or cracking security mechanisms to gain access</li>\n                                <li>Gathering data for analysis</li>\n                            </ul></li> \n                            <li>Performing analysis to determine the traffic being broadcast over the network,\n                                including sniffing for user names, passwords and credit card information</li>\n                                <li>Providing recommendations to mitigate security vulnerabilities throughout the\n                                    process and\n                                    communicate any identified high-risk vulnerabilities</li>\n                        </ul>\n\n                        <p class=\"homep\">This test helps determine an organization&#39;s security policy compliance, its employee&#39;s\n                            security awareness and the organization&#39;s ability to identify and respond to security\n                            incidents.</p>    \n                        <p>Actions include:</p>    \n                        <ul class=\"self\">\n                           <li>The process includes gathering information about the target before the test\n                            (reconnaissance)</li> \n                            <li>identifying possible entry points including the use of social engineering,\n                                attempting to break in and reporting the findings. The objective of penetration\n                                testing is to determine exploitable security weak</li>\n                        </ul>\n                     </div>\n                     </div>\n        \n        \n                     <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-13\">INTRUSION DETECTION PREVENTION AND SERVICES (IDPS)</p>\n        \n                     <div class=\"row\">\n                            <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                                    <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/intrusion.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n                                  </div>\n                       <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n                         <p class=\"homep\">\n                            This is necessary to monitor systems, networks, application logs for any\n        abnormal activities or potential threats, analyzing information and events perceived\n        as suspicious activities. Gauging these activities helps in identifying and forming\n        incident responses, which are further actionable. Main objectives of this service are:</p>\n                <ul class=\"self\">\n                    <li>SOLID SECURITY</li>\n                    <li>ELEVATED SERVICE LEVELS</li>\n                    <li>COMPLIANCE</li>\n                    <li>COST EFFECTIVE</li>\n                    <li>EASILY ADAPTABLE</li>\n                </ul>     \n                <p class=\"homep\">Intrusion prevention is the process of performing intrusion detection and then\n                    stopping the detected incidents. These security measures are available as intrusion\n                    detection systems (IDS) and intrusion prevention systems (IPS), which become part\n                    of your network to detect and stop potential incidents.</p> \n                    <p class=\"homep\">The main purpose of an intrusion prevention system is to identify malicious activity,\n                        log information about this activity and attempt to block/stop and report it. We have\n                        developed a proven, repeatable methodology for the successful deployment and\n                        ongoing management of intrusion prevention security (IPS) devices by:</p>   \n                        <ul class=\"self\">\n                            <li>Conducting an architecture review including technical and operational\n                                components to determine the right IPS for your organization</li>\n                            <li>Developing a configuration design to ensure that systems are properly\n                                monitored</li>   \n                         <li>Staging the IPS and preloading the configuration</li> \n                         <li>Assisting with the deployment of the IPS</li>\n                         <li>Providing tuning and ongoing management of the IPS and integrating the\n                            IDS/IPS logs to SIEM</li>\n                        </ul> \n                        <p>Tools- Cisco Fire sight, Security Onion, Suricata, OSSEC</p>          \n                           </div>\n                            </div>\n        \n        \n\n                            <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-14\">CLOUD SERVICES</p>\n\n<div class=\"row\">\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n        <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/cloud.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n      </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">\n        A cloud service can dynamically scale to meet the needs of its users, and because the\n        service provider supplies the hardware and software necessary for the service, there’s no\n        need for a company to provision or deploy its own resources or allocate IT staff to manage\n        the service.\n    </p>\n   <p class=\"homep\">Examples of cloud services include online data storage and backup solutions, Web-based\n    e-mail services, hosted office suites and document collaboration services, database\n    processing, managed technical support services and more.</p>\n   <p class=\"homep\">CySpace helps customers in creating an environment that works for companies around the\n    world. Our Cloud security solutions provide multiple levels of control in a network\n    infrastructure for protection.</p>\n    <p class=\"homep\">At CySpace Global™ we offer Cloud Security services and solutions which will detect threats\n        on the cloud environment monitor and the user behavior when they upload or download data\n        from the cloud providers. Also, it helps in protecting the applications hosted on the cloud\n        platform.</p>\n    <p class=\"homep\">To Enhance cloud security Posture CySpace Global™ Protects the client infrastructure by\n            continuously monitoring the user behavior and Network traffic, this will help in detecting\n            malicious activity by this we can Identify and Prevent data breaches</p>\n    <!-- <p class=\"color\">CySpace Global™ provides all kinds of Cloud services required for your organization's needs.</p>   -->\n        <p class=\"color\">CySpace Global™ provides all kinds of Cloud services required for your organization's needs.</p>      \n   </div>\n   </div>\n\n   <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-15\">CLOUD MIGRATION</p>\n\n<div class=\"row\">\n    <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n        <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/cloud-migration.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n      </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">An organization&#39;s cloud migration process often involves merging an on-site IT\n        infrastructure with a hybrid cloud solution, which we provide. Hybrid cloud solutions transition\n        between one or more cloud providers and usually provide on-demand and provisioned\n        server space, applications, and services.</p>\n    <p class=\"homep\">Cloud migration is critical for achieving real-time and updated performance and\n        efficiency. Thus, cloud migration requires careful analysis, planning, and execution to ensure\n        the cloud solution&#39;s compatibility with organizational requirements</p>    \n\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-16\">CLOUD INTEGRATION</p>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n            <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/cloud integration.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n          </div>\n      <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n        <p class=\"homep\">Integration is just slightly younger than the creation of software itself. The creation of\n            data was immediately followed by the need to move it, combine it and orchestrate it, rather\n            than it being confined to place it was created.</p>\n        <p class=\"homep\">Cloud integration platforms are used in organizations and IT environments where\n            some form of data, application or infrastructure is sourced from the cloud. Typically, a cloud\n            integration platform must provide a direct and reliable connection between on-site and cloud\n            environments, as well as integration and interconnectivity of different applications, platform\n            compatibility and the security and integrity of all data that passes between different systems.</p>    \n    \n        </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-17\">CLOUD SECURITY</p>\n\n        <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/cloud security_2.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n              </div>\n          <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n            <p class=\"homep\">Maintaining the security of data in the cloud extends beyond securing the cloud itself.\n                Cloud users must protect access to the cloud that can be gained from data stored on mobile\n                devices or carelessness with login credentials. Another cloud security issue is that data\n                stored on a cloud-hosted in another country may be subject to different regulations and\n                privacy measures. CySpace Global™ offers solutions to mitigate exactly these kinds of\n                scenarios.</p>    \n        \n            </div>\n            </div>\n\n           \n\n            <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-18\">IDENTITY & ACCESS MANAGEMENT</p>\n\n<div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/integrated Identity _ access mngmt.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n              </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">\n        IAM refers to a framework of policies and technologies for ensuring that the proper people in\nan enterprise have the appropriate access to technology resources.\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"homep\">CySpace Global&trade; provides IAM services with different frameworks for business processes,\n        policies, and technologies that facilitate the management of electronic or digital identities.\n        With an IAM framework in place, information technology (IT) managers can control user\n        access to critical information within their organizations.\n        Tools - SailPoint, RSA, IBM, NetIQ IDM, RSA SecurID, Okta Identity Management, Oracle\n        Identity Management</p>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"color\">We keep watch, so you don’t have to.</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-19\">INTEGRATED IDENTITY AND ACCESS MANAGEMENT</p>\n\n<div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/integrated Identity _ access mngmt.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n              </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">\n        Integrated access management (IAM) is a combination of business\nprocesses, policies, and technologies that allows organizations to provide secure\naccess to confidential data. IAM software is used by enterprises to control the flow of\nsensitive data in and out of the network. Advantages are as follows:</p>\n<ul class=\"self\">\n    <li>It’s almost impossible to enforce policies consistently across an organization\n        with fragmented systems</li>\n    <li>Manually managing access and permissions makes the system very hard to\n        scale, not to mention prone to human error that can have potentially\n        damaging consequences</li>\n    <li>Making it hard for users to navigate different access systems can stifle\n        business productivity and increase workload for IT and helpdesk teams.</li>\n</ul>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-20\">USER ACTIVITY MANAGEMENT</p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                    <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/user-activity-management.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid imgmar\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n                  </div>\n      <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n        <p class=\"homep\">\n            Many organizations implement user activity monitoring tools to help detect\nand stop insider threats, whether unintentional or malicious intent. By implementing\nuser activity monitoring, enterprises can more readily identify suspicious behavior\nand mitigate risks before they result in data breaches, or at least in time to minimize\ndamages.</p>\n   <p class=\"homep\">Sometimes called user activity tracking, user activity monitoring is a form of\n    surveillance but serves as a proactive review of end-user activity to determine\n    misuse of access privileges or data protection policies either through ignorance or\n    malicious intent.</p>>\n        </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-21\">IDENTITY ADMINISTRATION</p>\n        <div class=\"row\">\n                <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                        <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/Identity administration.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n                      </div>\n          <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n            <p class=\"homep\">\n                <b>Identity Administration</b> is the process of managing the lifecycle of identity\nand entitlements associated with those identities. It uses a combination of tools that\nprovide automated identity administration and manual processes fulfilled by\napplication administrators (e.g. account and access provisioning for a new\nemployee).</p>\n               <ul class=\"self\">\n                   <li>Record, capture and authenticate user login information (usernames,\n                    passwords, certificates, etc.)</li>\n                   <li>Manage the employee database of users and job roles</li>\n                   <li>Allow for addition, deletion, and change of individual users and broader job\n                    roles</li>       \n                   <li>Provide a history of login and systems access for audit purposes</li>       \n                   <li>Allow for properly-segmented definitions and access controls for every part of\n                    the business's systems and data</li>       \n                   <li>Track user activities across all systems and data</li> \n                   <li>Report on user activities</li> \n                   <li>Enforce systems access policies</li>                \n               </ul> \n            </div>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-22\">PRIVILEGED ACCOUNT MANAGEMENT</p>\n            <div class=\"row\">\n                    <div class=\"col-md-12 title\">\n                            <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/privilege-account-management.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n                          </div>\n              <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n                <p class=\"homep\">Privileged user accounts are significant targets for attack as they have\n                    elevated permissions, access to confidential information and the ability to change\n                    settings. If compromised, a large amount of damage could be made to organizational\n                    operations. Types of accounts that implement PAM can include emergency\n                    cybersecurity procedures, local administrative, Microsoft Active Directory, application\n                    or service, and domain administrator accounts.</p>\n                </div>\n                </div>\n                <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-23\">DATA LOSS PREVENTION</p>\n                <div class=\"row\">\n                        <div class=\"col-md-6 title\">\n                                <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/data-loss-prevention.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n                              </div>\n                  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n                    <p class=\"homep\">DLP is a method of inspecting and keeping sensitive data from leaving the\n                        allowed perimeter. DLP has the following key features:</p>\n                        <ul class=\"self\">\n                            <li>It is configurable with automated remediation. From a financial perspective,\n                                this can significantly reduce the expense associated with remediation.\n                                Automatic remediation may differ depending on the kind of activity involved.\n                                For instance, the user may opt to encrypt, quarantine, block and/or notify the\n                                sender in the event of an email.</li>\n                            <li>It is able to transfer data to a safe location if the data is found to be located in\n                                an unprotected area.</li>\n                            <li>It removes the need for manual user lookups using LDAP server/active\n                                directory. This feature is common among all DLP manufacturers.</li>\n                        </ul>\n                    </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-24\">GOVERNANCE & COMPLIANCE</p>\n\n<div class=\"row\">\n    <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n        <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/governance Compliance.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n  \n      </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">\n        A well-planned GRC strategy comes with lots of benefits: improved decision-making, more\n        optimal IT investments, elimination of silos, and reduced fragmentation among divisions and\n        departments, to name a few.\n    </p>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-25\">COMPLIANCE REPORTING</p>\n\n<div class=\"row\">\n    <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n        <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/compliance-reporting.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n  \n      </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">\n        Compliance reports are done by us if required. We have a team which is\n        tasked with looking at the regulations a company is subject to and determining\n        whether they’re achieving compliance through the processes and controls they’ve put\n        in place. Compliance officers are responsible for ensuring that a business is\n        complying with national and international regulations and assessing internal controls\n        and processes that ensure the rules are being followed. The purpose of the\n        compliance reports is to\n    </p>\n    <ul class=\"self\">\n        <li>hold processes accountable</li>\n        <li>not let them fall to the wayside and</li>\n        <li>alert and provoke change when there is a risk to compliance. Compliance\n            reports are often submitted to senior management, board and audit\n            committee members.</li>\n    </ul>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n\n\n\n    <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-26\">PHISHING RISK ASSESSMENT</p>\n<div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n                <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/Phishing assestment.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n          \n            </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">\n        Phishing attacks are emails that claim to be from a legitimate sender in order\nto obtain sensitive information such as usernames and passwords, credit cards and\nother personal information. Phishing emails can also contain malicious attachments\ndesigned to infect computers and mobile devices.\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"homep\">CySpace Global™ offers Phishing and Risk Assessment, will not only\n        measure your users’ awareness but also measure the risk of a successful breach\n        and resilience against an attack.</p>\n        <ul class=\"self\">\n            <li>It measures the risk of a successful phishing attack against your organization.</li>\n            <li>It lets you measure your organization’s resilience against phishing attacks\n                over time</li>\n        </ul>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <p class=\"title3 text-center\" id=\"section-27\">USER ACTIVITY REVIEW</p>\n<div class=\"row\">\n        <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n                <img src=\"../../../../assets/cyspace-images/it-risk-and-security/User activity review.jpg\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Responsive image\">\n          \n            </div>\n  <div class=\"col-md-12 title1\">\n    <p class=\"homep\">Any level of monitoring can accumulate large amounts of data. The goal of\n        any user activity monitoring program should be to find and filter out actionable\n        information that’s valuable in data protection efforts. With effective processes in\n        place, you can immediately detect and investigate suspicious user activity.</p>\n        <p>You can also find out if users are uploading sensitive data to public clouds,\n            utilizing non-approved services and applications, or engaging in any other type of\n            risky activity while using the company network or resources. User activity monitoring\n            tools are also helpful in ensuring that employees do not take any of your company&#39;s\n            confidential information when they are leaving the company.</p>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"color\">Innovative security services for all ur&#39;s Security needs</p>\n    </div>\n");
